5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 78, L.D. 142, “An Act to Prohibit
10 Financial Institutions from Charging Multiple Fees for Attempted Withdrawals Involving
11 Insufficient Funds”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Bureau of Financial Institutions to Issue Guidance Related to
14 the Charging of Multiple Fees for Attempted Withdrawals Involving Insufficient
15 Funds'
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
17 'Sec. 1. Guidance related to charging multiple fees for attempted
18 withdrawals involving insufficient funds. Resolved: That, no later than January 1,
19 2026, the Department of Professional and Financial Regulation, Bureau of Financial
20 Institutions shall issue written guidance to state-chartered financial institutions and credit
21 unions on the charging of multiple fees for attempted withdrawals involving insufficient
22 funds. Before developing the written guidance required by this section, the bureau shall
23 review any guidance issued by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation and the National
24 Credit Union Administration related to overdraft and insufficient funds fees and consult
25 with statewide associations representing state-chartered financial institutions and credit
26 unions.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill with
3311 a resolve. The amendment directs the Department of Professional and Financial Regulation,
3322 Bureau of Financial Institutions to issue guidance, no later than January 1, 2026, to
